Summary of Amendments Adopted by House
The Committee Amendments Proposed by House Committee on Agriculture, Forestry,
Aquaculture, and Rural Development to the original bill:
1. Transfer the requirement to conduct a statewide study to identify and map food
deserts from the Department of Agriculture and Forestry to the LSU AgCenter.
2. Transfer the responsibility of implementing and updating a public database with
certain geospatial mapping, population, and demographic information from the
Department of Agriculture and Forestry to the LSU AgCenter.
3. Shift the responsibility of submitting an annual report to the legislature that
includes a summary of any progress, barriers, outcomes, and any other
recommended statutory or budgetary changes from the Department of
Agriculture and Forestry to the LSU AgCenter.
4. Make technical changes.
